// bisect: GIR/emit bug (interp/node-walk != fused). The `%` operator lowers via gir::arith to an unguarded GirOp::Bin{op: BinOp::Mod}; the node-walk uses netidx's checked_rem which detects the i64::MIN % -1 overflow, the fused backends do not.
// interp/jit: Verified: `graphix-fuzz check` reports DIVERGENCE (interp: Timeout, fused: Value(i64:0), jit: Value(i64:0)) stably across 4 runs. Program typechecks cleanly (`graphix --check` exit 0). Deterministic — only i64 literals and the `%` operator; no rand/sys::time/sys::net/sys::fs, and no lambda/abstract 
// root_cause: Signed remainder overflow (i64::MIN % -1) handled inconsistently across backends. (1) Node-walk: node/op.rs dispatches to netidx Value::rem -> checked_rem (netidx-value/src/op.rs:708), whose `checked` macro arm (op.rs:234-239) calls Rust i64::checked_rem, returning None on the MIN%-1 overflow -> Value::error("arithmetic error"); the error Value yields no result so the runtime times out. (2) Fused interp: gir_interp.rs:1985 lowers BinOp::Mod to Rust wrapping_rem, which returns 0 for MIN%-1. (3) JIT: gir_jit.rs:6276 lowers BinOp::Mod to cranelift srem, also 0. The lowering site is gir::arith in 

